The President addresses the extreme cold weather and warns that it is a serious weather alert. The affected areas range from Oklahoma to Wyoming and Wyoming to Maine. The President encourages everyone to heed local warnings and provides the website Weather.gov for more information. He mentions that his team is prepared to help communities cope with the storm. The President also advises people to leave if they have travel plans and not to take the storm lightly. He mentions that he will be briefed by FEMA and the National Weather Service. The President concludes by thanking everyone and wishing them a Merry Christmas.